docs.title: BigInt

docs.title: Currency
docs.description: A field whose value is an ISO-4217 currency.

docs.title: Date
docs.description: A date string, such as 2007-12-03, compliant with the full-date format outlined in section 5.6 of the RFC 3339 profile of the ISO 8601 standard for representation of dates and times using the Gregorian calendar.

docs.title: DateTime
docs.description: A date-time string at UTC, such as 2007-12-03T1030Z, compliant with the date-time format outlined in section 5.6 of the RFC 3339 profile of the ISO 8601 standard for representation of dates and times using the Gregorian calendar.

docs.title: Duration
docs.description: A string representing a duration conforming to the ISO8601 standard,

docs.title: Hexadecimal
docs.description: A field whose value is a hexadecimal.

docs.title: HSL
docs.description: A field whose value is a CSS HSL color.

docs.title: IPv4
docs.description: A field whose value is a IPv4 address.

docs.title: ISBN
docs.description: A field whose value is a ISBN-10 or ISBN-13 number.

docs.title: JSON
docs.description: The JSON scalar type represents JSON values as specified by ECMA-404.

docs.title: JSONObject
docs.description: The JSONObject scalar type represents JSON objects as specified by ECMA-404.

docs.title: JWT
docs.description: A field whose value is a JSON Web Token (JWT).

docs.title: Latitude
docs.description: A field whose value is a valid decimal degrees latitude number (53.471).

docs.title: LocalDate
docs.description: A local date string (i.e., with no associated timezone) in YYYY-MM-DD format, e.g. 2020-01-01. The value is serialized and deserialized as a string as a signal to both clients and resolvers that special care must be taken with the value when converting it to any date/time type that includes a timezone, e.g., a JavaScript Date.

docs.title: LocalEndTime
docs.description: A local time string (i.e., with no associated timezone) in 24-hr HHss[.SSS]] format, e.g. 14252500 as a valid value to indicate midnight of the following day. This is useful when using the scalar to represent the exclusive upper bound of a time block.

docs.title: LocalTime
docs.description: A local time string (i.e., with no associated timezone) in 24-hr HHss[.SSS]] format, e.g. 142525:06.123. The seconds and milliseconds portions are optional. Like the LocalDate scalar, the value is serialized and deserialized as a string as a signal to both clients and resolvers that special care must be taken with the value when converting it to any date/time type that includes a date or timezone, e.g., a JavaScript Date.

docs.title: Longitude
docs.description: A field whose value is a valid decimal degrees longitude number (53.471).

docs.title: MAC
docs.description: A field whose value is a IEEE 802 48-bit MAC address.

docs.title: NegativeFloat
docs.description: Floats that will have a value less than 0. Uses parseFloat().

docs.title: NegativeInt
docs.description: Integers that will have a value less than 0. Uses parseInt().

docs.title: NonEmptyString
docs.description: A field whose value can accept any string except empty ones. It will trim any additional white space before validation. This is useful for required strings that you wish to also force a value for. "" or " " are both considered invalid values.

docs.title: NonNegativeFloat
docs.description: Floats that will have a value of 0 or more. Uses parseFloat().

docs.title: NonNegativeInt
docs.description: Integers that will have a value of 0 or more. Uses parseInt().

docs.title: NonPositiveFloat
docs.description: Floats that will have a value of 0 or less. Uses parseFloat().

docs.title: NonPositiveInt
docs.description: Integers that will have a value of 0 or less. Uses parseInt().

docs.title: ObjectID
docs.description: A field whose value conforms to the mongodb object id format as explained in the documentation

docs.title: PhoneNumber
docs.description: A field whose value conforms to the standard E.164 format as specified in

docs.title: Port
docs.description: A field whose value is a valid TCP port within the range of 0 to 65535.

docs.title: PositiveFloat
docs.description: Floats that will have a value greater than 0. Uses parseFloat().

docs.title: PositiveInt
docs.description: Integers that will have a value greater than 0. Uses parseInt().

docs.description: A field whose value is a CSS RGB color.

docs.title: RGBA
docs.description: A field whose value is a CSS RGBA color.

docs.title: SafeInt
docs.description: This scalar behaves just like the native GraphQLInt scalar, but it allows integers that require more than 32-bits. Any integer that is considered "safe" in JavaScript (i.e.  9,007,199,254,740,991) is considered a valid value. But if you need more than 52-bits, you should use BigInt.

docs.title: Time
docs.description: A time string at UTC, such as 1030Z, compliant with the full-time format outlined in section 5.6 of the RFC 3339 profile of the ISO 8601 standard for representation of dates and times using the Gregorian calendar.

docs.title: Timestamp
docs.description: The javascript Date as integer. Type represents date and time as number of milliseconds from start of UNIX epoch.

docs.title: URL
docs.description: A field whose value conforms to the standard URL format as specified in

docs.title: USCurrency
docs.description: A US currency string, such as \$21.25.

docs.title: UtcOffset
docs.description: String that will have a value of format hh:mm. List of tz database time zones.

docs.title: UUID
docs.description: A field whose value is a generic Universally Unique Identifier.

docs.title: Void
docs.description: The Void scalar type represents no value being returned
